Feature: Document Variables


@doc_vars
@vars_read
Scenario Outline: Updates CDB document variables with values from CDB
    GIVEN a <application_name> file <source_file> exists as a document in CDB
    WHEN the document gets loaded from CDB
    AND the metadata of the document gets updated with values from CDB
    THEN the metadata is updated in the document
    Examples:
        | application_name | source_file         |
        | excel            | test_vars_read.xlsx |
        | powerpoint       | test_vars_read.pptx |
        | visio            | test_vars_read.vsdx |
        | word             | test_vars_read.docx |


@doc_vars
@vars_write
Scenario Outline: Transfers values of CDB document variables to CDB
    GIVEN a <application_name> file <source_file> exists as a document in CDB
    WHEN the document gets loaded from CDB
    AND the metadata of the document gets transfered to CDB
    THEN the metadata is updated in CDB
    Examples:
        | application_name | source_file          |
        | excel            | test_vars_write.xlsx |
        | powerpoint       | test_vars_write.pptx |
        | visio            | test_vars_write.vsdx |
        | word             | test_vars_write.docx |


@doc_vars
@vars_table
Scenario Outline: Updates a CDB document variable table with values from CDB
    GIVEN a <application_name> file <source_file> exists as a document in CDB
    AND the document has multiple status protocol entries
    WHEN the document gets loaded from CDB
    AND the metadata of the document gets updated with values from CDB
    THEN the metadata is updated in the table in the document
    Examples:
        | application_name | source_file          |
        | excel            | test_vars_table.xlsx |
        | word             | test_vars_table.docx |
